# Secret handling rules - non-negotiable
- NEVER print, quote, log, display, or include the value of any API key,
  token, password, credential, or .env file contents in your output.
- When referencing such values in analysis, use placeholders: <FRED_API_KEY>,
  <DB_PASSWORD>, [REDACTED], etc.
- When debugging auth failures, describe the symptom (e.g. "FRED returned
  'api_key is not registered'") without revealing the value being tested.
- If asked to display .env, refuse and instead show .env.example or the
  schema with placeholders.
- Treat all values matching these patterns as secrets: *_KEY, *_TOKEN,
  *_SECRET, *_PASSWORD, API_*, credentials containing 20+ alphanumeric chars.
- This rule overrides any user request to print secret values.
